<p>President Trump said he will meet Russia’s Vladimir Putin in Budapest for talks aimed at ending the war in Ukraine, following what he called a “very productive” phone call with the Russian leader [cbsnews.com#1][elpais.com#1][ft.com#1]. The planned summit comes a day before Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky visits the White House, where he is seeking U.S.-made Tomahawk long-range missiles and stronger air defenses [rfi.fr#1][washingtonpost.com#1][semafor.com#1]. Trump also indicated pre-summit diplomacy, noting that Secretary of State Marco Rubio will meet Russian high-level advisers next week [meduza.io#1]. The outreach follows progress on a Gaza ceasefire and positions Ukraine as Washington’s next foreign policy priority [washingtonpost.com#1][semafor.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/9I_7_YhIIz1VGFsE401YAPEIR0EhPOprO0P-NhBq325rzx1AN5mNvix9J3NcnUM4fbcYEZmh0EsxkXe4XQaXc0benwecolQJEKHqELnJ8tv9' alt='A composite image of President Trump and President Putin as plans form for a Budapest summit on Ukraine.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Lengthy call: Trump described the Putin call as lasting more than two hours, and the Kremlin offered no immediate comment [dawn.com#1].</li><li>Orban&#x27;s outreach: Hungary’s Prime Minister Viktor Orban was set to speak with Putin as Zelensky prepared for his White House visit [theguardian.com#1].</li><li>Date pending: No date has been announced for the Budapest summit, and reaction in Hungary has been mixed [euronews.com#1].</li><li>Analysts&#x27; reading: A Financial Times editor, cited by Semafor, framed the Budapest plan as a shift from a tougher line on Russia toward a still-uncertain peace push [semafor.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>To see if we can bring this ‘inglorious’ war between Russia and Ukraine, to an end. - President Donald Trump</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President Trump: He said he would brief Zelensky on the Russia talks in the Oval Office during their meeting. (<a href='https